caption: The açaí bowls here are actually pretty good. I never struck myself as an açaí bowl guy who takes the time to get the accents typed out, but here I am typing açaí with a ‘ç’ and an ‘í.’  I assume the way these things work is that if you try one, you’ve tried em’ all, so it’s safe to assume that they’re all pretty good here. The empanada was exceedingly edible as well. To my surprise, the Mediterranean Delight sandwich was the star of the show for me.  I’m probably never gonna go back again because I exclusively eat yogurt or eggs for breakfast these days. Probably won’t, but might.

Great spot for smoothies, açaí bowls, empanadas, or arepas. I typically get an arepa or açaí bowl, depending on what I’m in the mood for. They have some creative combinations on their menu and you can always mix and match ingredients (but it will cost a premium for substitutions). The wait is also typically very long. Overall, I’ve been satisfied with my experiences here and think it’s worth the wait.
Love this place! Great atmosphere (cozy and relaxing) and a large fantastic menu, especially the smoothies and empanadas. Very good service too. Support this small business!!

Outstanding little restaurant and smoothie bar. They have a great selection of tasty food and drinks. They also have a whole menu and a half of healthy fruit and veggie smoothies, acai and granola bowls, and other healthy items. Highly recommended, relatively new and in a booming location. Support great small businesses especially healthy ones.  We loved the Tropical Green and Multi V smoothies. The Empanadas were very tasty as well as the veggie chili. Anything on the menu is most likely amazing though. 5 stars!

When you walk in there's a strong smell of food or something that's not very pleasant and there was no one up front either to greet you.  The gentleman that helped us came from the back and didn't really greet us and when my husband asked what the base for the smoothies is (water,  milk or 100% fruit) he didn't really give an answer so my husband didn't order anything.  I ordered the green Gloria bowl. It took a while, maybe 15 minutes, for me to get my bowl but it was delicious! I think that it must've just been the one guy running the whole place by himself and there was already a table of customers there so my theory is that he read making their order before mine that's why my bowl took so long. I would come back and try other things from their menu. They have a decent variety of items that sound tasty!! I just think they just need more staff to properly run this place otherwise be prepared to wait a few minutes for your order.

I’ve always wanted to try açaí bowls and so I always tried to find places where they sell it and a lot of them were saying the açaí bowls were about 12 dollars for a small one. I found this place “Fruit Paradise” and I recommend this place and to try the açaí bowls of you haven’t! You won’t regret it. The workers are super humble, I really loved the açaí bowl, super delicious for only $5.75.  Acai bowls is a smoothie bowl that has açaí. Açaí is a Brazilian fruit and this açaí bowl is very healthy. It’s topped with granola, fruits and coconut flakes and honey, there’s different types of açaí bowls with the same price.
